metatags.og:title: Photo of Putin wearing crinkled suit has circulated online since 2017
metatags.og:description: An image of Russian President Vladimir Putin has been shared thousands of times online alongside a claim he "has started to wear a bulletproof vest" after Moscow's invasion of Ukraine. Part of Putin's wrinkled suit jacket was circled in the posts as evidence for the claim. The photo has been shared in a false context: it has circulated in reports since mid-2017, almost five years before Russian troops invaded Ukraine.

htmlSnippet: Nov 3, 2022 ... While social media have played a role in previous wars – for example, Russian soldiers were identified on the battlefield in the Donbas region ...

metatags.og:title: Disinformation and Russia’s war of aggression against Ukraine
metatags.og:description: This paper provides an overview of how the Russia's war of aggression against Ukraine illustrates immediate threats posed by disinformation, as well as governance responses to countering it. It focuses on disinformation in relation to the Russian armed aggression of Ukraine, including actors, tools and narratives used to justify the invasion and maintain support for the war. The paper also identifies government efforts to counter the spread of disinformation, including efforts to ensure the spread of accurate content, promote international co-operation, and support civil society and media actors to build resilience to the spread of false and misleading content.
metatags.twitter:creator: @OECD

metatags.og:title: Seana Davis on Twitter
metatags.og:description:
“A viral post claims to show proof that Putin has recently started wearing a bulletproof vest.

But the image is old. It dates to August 2017 when he  flew to Lake Baikal for his election campaign.”

socialmediaposting.articlebody: A viral post claims to show proof that Putin has recently started wearing a bulletproof vest. But the image is old. It dates to August 2017 when he flew to Lake Baikal for his election campaign.
We also can't definitively say whether the photograph simply shows a crinkle in Putin's suit or indeed whether he was wearing some sort of vest at the time. Take a look ⬇️
